	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Feb 22nd 6:04 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>All &quot;facts&quot; given here are my experience and opinions, and are NOT to be taken as holy writ (like anyone here would do that!&nbsp;&nbsp;:)<br><br>What I did with the multitude of spells is this:  I started with your typical set of level 1 spells (some kind person gave me 1 pp at level one, which kept me well supplied for about five levels.  it wasn't much to them, but it was a HUGE ammount of money to a newbie!).  I memmed all of these, every time I died (and oh, boy did I die a lot).  I didn't know which ones I was going to use, and which ones I was going to find useless, so I memmed them all.<br><br>By the time I got my level 5 spells, I had a better idea of how I was going to be playing a cleric (I was grouping Orc Hill in Greater Faydark by this point), and so I selected my spells with that in mind.<br><br>Over the levels, I have replaced spells with their upgrades, but my basic gem setup has only changed once.  I had the following spells set up until just about two levels ago:<br>1)  Superior Healing<br>2)  Guard<br>3)  Force<br>4)  Valor<br>5)  Stun (yes, the original.  it doesn't do DD, and so can be used to assist chanters without breaking mez)<br>6)  Enstill<br>7)  Gate<br>8)  --changes--<br><br>This allowed me to perform both in groups and solo semi-effectively, with minimal changeout, all of it in slot 8 (which would change between my summon spells, Extinguish Fatigue, Bind Affinity, Revive, Greater Heal, etc.).<br><br>Only recently, I have changed my tactics.  I'm doing almost exclusively groups, and don't have the mana for stun and direct damage spells.  So gem 2 is now Symbol, and gem 5 is Extinguish Fatigue.  I left Enstill in place so I could help the tanks get mobs off of me.  Gem 8 still changes, but when I'm in group, it pretty much stays Greater Healing (for the casters, who don't need SupHeal at my level), unless someone needs to be Revived.<br><br>As for spell effects, yes, they go up with level.  This is most noticable with the heal spells, since they tell your target (and your target can tell you, if you ask) exactly how many points they were healed for.  In the levels since 24, my GHeal has gone from around 285 or 290 up to a heal for 315 or so.  Your HP/AC buffs also go up as you level.  This is solely based on your (the caster's) level, and has nothing to do with the level of the person you are casting on.<br><br>I have a hotkey set up (number 3, page 1, if you care) with the command &quot;/book&quot; which takes me directly to the book screen, and I then use escape or my stand key (num pad 0, best key I ever mapped) when I'm ready to cast.  The book goes away at 35, and you automatically meditate when you sit down after this level.<br><br>Your memorization time goes down as your meditation skill goes up.  You won't really notice a difference till about level 10 or 12, and these days I can change spells during combat without missing much.<br><br><br>Respectfully submitted under the eyes of the Mother of All,<br>Atheana Starfyre<br>Cleric of Tunare<br>Initiate of the 37th Circle<br>Veeshan Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
